## Material Selection

The final material selected was:

### **Aluminum 7475-T7651**
- \(E = 10 \times 10^6\ \text{psi}\)  
- \(\nu = 0.29\)  
- \( \sigma_u \approx 65\ \text{ksi}\)  
- \( K_{IC} \approx 46\ \text{ksi}\sqrt{\text{in}} \)

This alloy provided strong fatigue resistance and fracture toughness, allowing a narrower reduced section to enhance strain amplification.

---

## Finite Element Analysis (ANSYS)

The CAD model was imported into **ANSYS** for static structural simulation.

### Boundary Conditions
- **Drive end:** fully constrained over the top 0.40 in  
- **Applied load:** equivalent to 600 in·lbf torsion  

### Results Summary

| Quantity | FEM Value |
|---------|------------|
| Maximum Normal Stress | 133.75 ksi |
| Load-Point Deflection | 0.38077 in |
| Gauge-Location Strains (x, y, z) | \([-0.3059,\ -0.30605,\ 1.055]\) millistrain |

### Strain Contours

