---

## Sensitivity Prediction (mV/V)

Using the half-bridge approximation:

\[
\frac{V_{out}}{V_{in}} \approx \frac{k(2\varepsilon)}{4}
\]

Where \( k \approx 2.05 \).

**Final Result:**  
\[
\boxed{V_{out}/V_{in} \ge 1.0\ \text{mV/V}}
\]

The optimized design surpasses the required minimum sensitivity.

---

## Strain Gauge Selection

A suitable commercial gauge was selected based on grid size, available bonding area, and expected strain range.

### Selected Gauge
- **Model:** Vishay EA-06-125BZ-350  
- **Type:** Linear foil, 350 Ω  
- **Gauge Factor:** ≈ 2.05  

### Gauge Specifications

| Parameter | Value |
|----------|--------|
| Grid Length | 3.18 mm |
| Grid Width | 1.57 mm |
| Pattern | Linear foil |

This gauge provides stable, accurate measurement when configured as part of a half-bridge.

---

## Final Remarks

This project integrated analytical mechanics, CAD development, FEM validation, and strain-gauge selection into a complete mechanical instrumentation workflow.  
The redesigned wrench satisfies all structural safety requirements and **exceeds the original sensitivity target**, improving performance by more than a factor of two.

